# ðŸ“¡ tcpdump Cheatsheet

ðŸŽ¯ Common Options & Filters:
| **Command / Option**           | **Description**                                        | **Example**                  |
| ------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------- |
| `tcpdump -i INTERFACE`         | Capture packets on a specific network interface        | `tcpdump -i eth0`            |
| `tcpdump -w FILE`              | Write captured packets to a file (PCAP format)         | `tcpdump -w capture.pcap`    |
| `tcpdump -r FILE`              | Read packets from a capture file                       | `tcpdump -r traffic.pcap`    |
| `tcpdump -c COUNT`             | Capture a specific number of packets                   | `tcpdump -c 100`             |
| `tcpdump -n`                   | Don't resolve IP addresses                             | `tcpdump -n`                 |
| `tcpdump -nn`                  | Don't resolve IPs or port names                        | `tcpdump -nn`                |
| `tcpdump -v`, `-vv`, `-vvv`    | Increase verbosity level                               | `tcpdump -vv -i eth0`        |
| `tcpdump -s 0`                 | Capture full packets (no truncation)                   | `tcpdump -s 0 -w full.pcap`  |
| `tcpdump port PORT_NUMBER`     | Filter packets on a specific port                      | `tcpdump port 80`            |
| `tcpdump src port PORT_NUMBER` | Filter packets from a specific source port             | `tcpdump src port 443`       |
| `tcpdump dst port PORT_NUMBER` | Filter packets to a specific destination port          | `tcpdump dst port 22`        |
| `tcpdump host IP_OR_HOSTNAME`  | Filter packets to/from a specific host                 | `tcpdump host 192.168.1.10`  |
| `tcpdump src host IP`          | Filter packets **from** a specific source IP           | `tcpdump src host 10.0.0.5`  |
| `tcpdump dst host IP`          | Filter packets **to** a specific destination IP        | `tcpdump dst host 10.0.0.10` |
| `tcpdump PROTOCOL`             | Filter packets by protocol (`ip`, `ip6`, `icmp`, etc.) | `tcpdump icmp`               |
